e arguments are directly relevant to the study of women in other insurgence and terrorist movements. The book will be of interest to scholars and students of history, Hispanic studies, gender studies, anthropology and politics, as well as to journalists and readers interested in women’s participation in contemporary conflicts and terrorist movements.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aNationalismzSpainzPaís VascoxHistory. 0aWomenxPolitical activityzSpainzPaís VascoxHistory. 0aWomen, Basque. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh  aETA.  aarmed activists.  acombatants.  acultural movements.  afeminism.  agender politics.  amotherhood.  aprison.  aradical Basque nationalism.  awomen's nationalist activism.1 aHamilton, Carrie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779144340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847791443423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847791443/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles